<section
  class="py-8 md:py-20"
  style="background-color: hsl(220 14% 96%); width: 100vw; position: relative; left: 50%; right: 50%; margin-left: -50vw; margin-right: -50vw;"
>
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 md:px-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">

      <!-- Ad Banner top -->
      <div
        class="rounded-lg px-4 md:px-6 py-6 text-center mb-8"
        style="background: #F3F4F6; border: 2px dashed #D1D5DB;"
      >
        <p
          class="text-xs md:text-sm mb-2"
          style="color: #6B7280; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;"
        >
          Advertisement
        </p>
        <div class="rounded h-20 md:h-32 lg:h-40" style="background: #E5E7EB;"></div>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h2
          class="mt-6 mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.6rem, 3vw, 1.875rem); font-weight: 700; color: hsl(107 76% 26%); line-height: 1.2; letter-spacing: -0.02em;"
        >
          Types of Xbox Gamertags: Find a Name Style That Fits You
        </h2>

        <p
          class="mb-6"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;"
        >
          A good Xbox gamertag is not just about availability. It should match your style, feel natural on your profile, and still look good after the first week. That is why it helps to explore different gamertag styles before choosing one.
        </p>

        <p
          class="mb-6"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;"
        >
          Some players want funny Xbox gamertags, while others prefer cool, clean, dark, aesthetic, or competitive names. The best choice depends on how you want your Xbox identity to feel in lobbies, on leaderboards, and across other gaming platforms.
        </p>

        <p
          class="mb-6"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;"
        >
          Use the sections below to explore popular Xbox gamertag categories and get a better idea of what kind of name fits you best.
        </p>

        <!-- Ad Banner -->
        <div
          class="rounded-lg p-4 md:p-6 text-center my-8"
          style="background: #F3F4F6; border: 2px dashed #D1D5DB;"
        >
          <p
            class="text-xs md:text-sm mb-2"
            style="color: #6B7280; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;"
          >
            Advertisement
          </p>
          <div class="rounded h-20 md:h-32 lg:h-40" style="background: #E5E7EB;"></div>
        </div>

        <h3
          class="mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem); font-weight: 700; color: hsl(107 76% 26%); line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: -0.01em;"
        >
          Xbox Gamertag Ideas by Style and Vibe
        </h3>

        <p
          class="mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;"
        >
          One of the easiest ways to choose a name is to start with the vibe you want. Do you want your Xbox gamertag to sound funny, stylish, dark, competitive, or simple?
        </p>

        <ul class="mb-6 space-y-2" style="list-style: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">Funny Xbox Gamertags:</strong> Great for players who want a name that feels playful, clever, or memorable.
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">Cool Xbox Gamertags:</strong> Clean, confident, and easy to picture on a profile or scoreboard.
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">Dark or Edgy Gamertags:</strong> A strong option for players who want a more serious or intense style.
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">Aesthetic Gamertags:</strong> Soft, clean, and stylish names that feel modern and visually appealing.
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">OG and Classic Gamertags:</strong> Short, simple names that feel timeless and easy to remember.
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">One-Word Gamertags:</strong> Minimal, strong, and often the easiest style to build a recognizable identity around.
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            <strong style="color: #111827;">Streamer and Brandable Gamertags:</strong> Names that can work across Xbox, Discord, Twitch, YouTube, and other platforms.
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p
          class="mb-6"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;"
        >
          If you are still testing ideas, start with your preferred style first, then use the generator to explore names that match that tone.
        </p>

        <!-- Ad Banner -->
        <div
          class="rounded-lg p-4 md:p-6 text-center my-8"
          style="background: #F3F4F6; border: 2px dashed #D1D5DB;"
        >
          <p
            class="text-xs md:text-sm mb-2"
            style="color: #6B7280; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;"
          >
            Advertisement
          </p>
          <div class="rounded h-20 md:h-32 lg:h-40" style="background: #E5E7EB;"></div>
        </div>

        <h3
          class="mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2.5vw, 1.5rem); font-weight: 700; color: hsl(107 76% 26%); line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: -0.01em;"
        >
          Xbox Gamertag Ideas by Identity
        </h3>

        <p
          class="mb-4"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;"
        >
          Some players prefer a name that reflects their identity more directly. That can help narrow the style and make the final name feel more personal.
        </p>

        <ul class="mb-6 space-y-2" style="list-style: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem;">
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            Xbox gamertags for guys
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            Xbox gamertags for girls
          </li>
          <li style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;">
            Gender-neutral Xbox gamertags
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p
          class="mb-6"
          style="font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif; font-size: clamp(15px, 2vw, 17px); line-height: 1.8; color: #374151;"
        >
          These categories do not limit you, but they can make the generator more useful if you already know the kind of tone you want.
        </p>

        <!-- Ad Banner -->
        <div
          class="rounded-lg p-4 md:p-6 text-center my-8"
          style="background: #F3F4F6; border: 2px dashed #D1D5DB;"
        >
          <p
            class="text-xs md:text-sm mb-2"
            style="color: #6B7280; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;"
          >
            Advertisement
          </p>
          <div class="rounded h-20 md:h-32 lg:h-40" style="background: #E5E7EB;"></div>
